{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"49f7d75e-26d0-4133-8a21-7a564b325c3f","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. Update NuGet packages:**\n- Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v4.6.0+** (you already have this ✅)\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` package\n- Keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n\n**2. Enable the new platform in your `.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. (Optional but recommended) Generate a test entry point:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests the same way:**\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n`dotnet test` detects `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` and uses the new platform automatically instead of VSTest.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter ≥4.6.0 already includes a Microsoft.Testing.Platform adapter, so no separate adapter package is needed.\n- If you use `dotnet test` with `--`, CLI args now follow [Microsoft.Testing.Platform syntax](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter`).\n- `.runsettings` files still work, but platform-specific config may differ.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c8ee2f73-6de2-439c-8534-4fc5416bea27","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure migration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":431,"requestId":"0BDB:3A1531:1E69E3:23A5B7:69F00428"},"id":"11207215-caf7-49e1-8873-e5072528675e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:53.686Z","parentId":"a3b4b352-d8d5-4c4d-887e-d9e7f66a9aa9"}
